# TODO completion tracking

When you implement or complete a task that corresponds to an item in [TODO.md](TODO.md):

1. **Update TODO.md in the same change set** (same edit/commit): change the relevant `- [ ]` to `- [x]`.
2. **When every item in a subsection is done**, add ✅ to that subsection header (e.g. `### 4.1 Data Persistence Testing ✅`).
3. **When a phase has all subsections complete**, update the phase header emoji to ✅ (e.g. `## Phase 4: Testing and Refinements ✅`).
4. Do this as part of the work that completes the task; do not wait for the user to request it.

Example: after implementing "Add error boundaries for external libraries", edit TODO.md and change
`- [ ] Add error boundaries for external libraries` to `- [x] Add error boundaries for external libraries`.
